               <p>1763. <persName id="def1-1763-18510818" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1763-18510818" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1763-18510818" type="surname" value="PRIOR"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1763-18510818" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOHN PRIOR</hi>
                  </persName> was <hi rend="italic">again</hi> indicted<rs id="t18510818-1763-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18510818-1763-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18510818-1763-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="embezzlement"></interp> for embezzling, on <rs id="t18510818-cd-3" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18510818-1763-offence-1 t18510818-cd-3"></join>21st June</rs>, 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; the moneys of <persName id="t18510818-name-1018" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1018" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1018" type="surname" value="SHAW"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1018" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18510818-1763-offence-1 t18510818-name-1018"></join>William Shaw</persName>, his master.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. ROBINSON</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">This was the indictment to which the evidence given in the first case applied.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PARRY</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">applied to withdraw the plea of</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
NOT GUILTY</hi>, <hi rend="italic">and put in a plea of</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">AUTREFOIS ACQUIT</hi>, <hi rend="italic">which he submitted he was entitled to do at any period within six days.</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. GURNEY</hi>, <hi rend="italic">after having consulted</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. JUSTICE WIGHT<lb></lb>MAN</hi>, <hi rend="italic">was of opinion that he could not receive the plea.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18510818-name-1019" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1019" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1019" type="surname" value="HOOD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1019" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM HOOD</persName>
                  </hi>. On 21st June I sold <hi rend="italic">Joe</hi> a load of clover, and sent the prisoner with him to receive the money—it was his duty when he had received it to pay it over to me—4<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. was the amount—I next saw him in the Old Kent-road, when he paid me 3<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. for the clover, and said that was all the money he had got, the old woman had not got any more, and the old man was not at home, and he would pay it in a fortnight, when he went that way.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PARRY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> How long after that did be remain in Mr. Shaw's service? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Till 28th—it was <hi rend="italic">Long Joe</hi> who bought the hay—I do not know where he is—Mr. Ostler is not <hi rend="italic">Long Joe</hi>—I did not sell it to Ostler—I have dealt with Mr. Ostler before, but not with <hi rend="italic">Joe.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> The prisoner had no authority to sell it to Mr. Ostler? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. ROBINSON</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> But he was to get the money and bring it back to you? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PARRY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> From <hi rend="italic">Joe</hi>? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> He was either to bring back the money or the hay.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="185108180181"></xptr>
               <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallCaps">ROBINSON</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> He was not to allow the hay to go out of his pesses<lb></lb>sion unless he got the money? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No; nothing was said about getting it from anybody else—the prisoner was not in the habit of selling hay for me, without I gave him directions—I did so occasionally, but not on this occasion Joe was not with the prisoner at first, but came afterwards—they would not tell me where they were going to take the hay.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18510818-name-1020" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1020" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1020" type="surname" value="OSTLER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1020" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM OSTLER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a carman, at 16, Earl-street, Finsbury. On 21st June I bought a load of hay—<hi rend="italic">Joe</hi> and the prisoner brought it together—I put the prisoner 4<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 7<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—he gave me this receipt, and put his cross to it (<hi rend="italic">produced: This was a bill headed</hi>, "Mr. Ostler, bought of Mr. Shaw," <hi rend="italic">amounting to</hi> 4<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 7<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; <hi rend="italic">settled, John Prior's mark</hi>)—I do not suppose I should hive bought it only I saw Mr. Shaw's name on the cart.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. GURNET</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">being of opinion upon this evidence that the money in question was not received by the prisoner in virtue of his employment, the Jury found</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">
                     <rs id="t18510818-1763-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18510818-1763-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510818-1763-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value=""></interp>NOT GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>.</p>
